In addition to the Ops Manager data listed above, the Collector provides
the following custom metadata:

  - **Environment type**- this is input by the CLI user; options
    include production, pre-production, development, and qa.
  - **List of files collected** - the list of the files created by the
    `collect` command
  - **Data collection timestamp** - the date at which the data was
    collected
  - **Collector tool version** - the version of the Collector used to
    collect data 

This data is stored in the `metadata` file.

## <a id="transmission"></a>Transmission

After the Collector collects files containing data, it transmits these
files to Pivotal and is stored securely. 

## <a id="security"></a>Security

  - The Collector uses HTTPS connections to communicate with an Ops
    Manager
  - The Collector transmits data using user-specific credentials to make
    an authenticated HTTPS request to Pivotal
  - All credentials can be passed as environment variables, reducing the
    chance of leakage

## <a id="storage"></a>Storage

Data is stored in Google Cloud Platform (GCP).
